detaileddescription.para: This function handles the read request 0x22 0x493B.

Function that reads the measure values of DID 0x493B (responsible for basic emergency arming level 1). If some of the parameter signals of DID are active, then the corresponding bit of DID will be set to active.
N/A
N/A
OpStatus
- Operation status range Dcm_OpStatusType resolution N/A unit N/A
*Data
- Buffer for copying response data range uint8 resolution N/A unit N/A
Std_ReturnType retVal - Value error code for DCM, standard return AUTOSAR type. range 0 - E_OK | 1 - E_NOT_OK, defined in AUTOSAR Standard. resolution N/A unit N/A
Globals
E_OK [in] - if all th signal parameters were succesfully read. MESSAGE_0x493B_ARRAY_SIZE [in]- Array size of message 0x493B RTE_E_OK [in] - Checks if the read of signals was succesful E_NOT_OK [in] - if any of the signal parameters couldn't be read properly or if Data is empty.
Input->Output-Correlation
E_OK indicates that all signal parameters were read succesfully. MESSAGE_0x493B_ARRAY_SIZE indicates the size of the array in which the value of signal parameters will be stored. RTE_E_OK indicates that the read of signals was succesful. E_NOT_OK indicates that at least one of the signal parameters couldn't be read properly.
reentrant No context task context thread safe No multicore safe No synchronous

This function handles the read request 0x22 0x198D.

Function that reads the measure values of DID 0x198D (responsible for inclination sensor (NGS) status: Sensor). If some of the parameter signals of DID are active, then the corresponding bit of DID will be set to active.
N/A
N/A
OpStatus
- Operation status range Dcm_OpStatusType resolution N/A unit N/A
*Data
- Buffer for copying response data range uint8 resolution N/A unit N/A
Std_ReturnType retVal - Value error code for DCM, standard return AUTOSAR type. range 0 - E_OK | 1 - E_NOT_OK, defined in AUTOSAR Standard. resolution N/A unit N/A
Globals
E_OK [in] - if all th signal parameters were succesfully read. MESSAGE_0x198D_ARRAY_SIZE [in]- Array size of message 0x198D. IpduStatus_DWASensors_01 [in] - Used to calculate the sensor timeout. Rte_StatusMask_TimeoutError [in] - Used to calculate the sensor timeout. E_NOT_OK [in] - if any of the signal parameters couldn't be read properly or if Data is empty. RTE_E_OK [in] - Checks if the read of signals was succesful
Input->Output-Correlation
E_OK indicates that all signal parameters were read succesfully. MESSAGE_0x198D_ARRAY_SIZE indicates the size of the array in which the value of signal parameters will be stored (auTempArray), the size of the array that will be stored in Data if there is no communication and the size of the array that will be stored in the Data if SWC is not coded . IpduStatus_DWASensors_01 and Rte_StatusMask_TimeoutError used to calculate if the sensor timeout is true or false (if FALSE, there is communication and if TRUE, there isn't). E_NOT_OK indicates that at least one of the signal parameters couldn't be read properly. RTE_E_OK indicates that the read of signals was succesful.

Handles the condition check read request for the Service (DID 0x154A - Parameter identification).

This function does extra condition checking, before the actual read request is called. Return value depends on the outcome of the condition check performed. Session check is done by DCM.
N/A
N/A
OpStatus
- Operation status. range Dcm_OpStatusType resolution N/A unit N/A
[in/out]
*ErrorCode - Error code which is forwarded to CAN. range Dcm_NegativeResponseCodeType resolution N/A unit N/A
Std_ReturnType retVal - Value error code for DCM, standard return AUTOSAR type. range 0 - DCM_E_OK | 1 - DCM_E_NOT_OK | 0x0AU - DCM_E_PENDING , defined in AUTOSAR Standard. resolution N/A unit N/A
Globals
DCM_E_OK [in] - This value is representing a successful operation. DCM_E_NOT_OK [in] - This value is representing a unsuccessful operation. K_LIN_DID_154A [in] - DID of DWA Sounder measure value 0x154A ConfigLinDiag_Read_Write_DID_buf [in/out] - Global buffer for LIN DK1/DK2 request and response data buffering K_SID22 [in] - Read request SID 0x22 K_LIN_DWA_SENSOR_ID [in] - Defines ID of LIN ECU : DWA SENSOR MESSAGE_0x154A_ARRAY_SIZE [in] - Array size of message 0x154A
Input->Output-Correlation
DCM_E_OK used to initialize retVal. DCM_E_NOT_OK used to set value of reVal when ErrorCode is a null pointer. K_LIN_DID_154A, ConfigLinDiag_Read_Write_DID_buf, K_SID22, K_LIN_DWA_SENSOR_ID, MESSAGE_0x154A_ARRAY_SIZE, DCM_E_NOT_OK are used to initialize tempLinDiagReq structure when ErrorCode is not a null pointer. In case of ErrorCode different than null pointer retVal is equal with return value of ConfigLinDiagReadWrite called with address of tempLinDiagReq structure.
reentrant No context DCM Task thread safe No multicore safe No synchronous
